\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Authorization Decision Process
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall require every County information system to hold a valid authorization decision before processing production data or maintaining persistent connectivity to the County production network.
 This policy implements the Authorize step of the NIST Risk Management Framework lifecycle adopted in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall base authorization decisions solely on the assessment results and audit findings delivered under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 current risk ratings and security categorization documentation maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
,
 and the status of any open Corrective Action Plans tracked under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 This policy does not establish a separate or parallel testing,
 assessment,
 or evidence-collection program.
 Where the IT Director determines that existing assessment coverage is insufficient to support an authorization decision,
 the IT Director shall direct the Assistant IT Director to schedule supplemental assessment activity through the mechanisms defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall compile the decision inputs and present them to the IT Director with a risk summary that identifies:
 the system or control under review,
 the security categorization,
 the assessment results and any open deficiencies,
 the current risk rating,
 and a recommendation.
 The IT Director shall review the compiled inputs and render one of the decision outcomes defined in Section 6.2.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Decision Outcomes
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall render one of the following decisions for each system or control submitted for authorization review.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Authorization to Operate
\series default
:
 Issued when 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 assessment results verify that controls are implemented correctly,
 operating as intended,
 and producing the desired outcome,
 and residual risk is within the risk tolerance defined in the Risk Management Strategy maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The system is approved for production operation.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Conditional Authorization
\series default
:
 Issued when residual risk exceeds tolerance but can be managed through documented compensating controls or time-bound conditions.
 The authorization decision record shall identify each condition,
 the compensating control or remediation action required,
 and the timeframe for resolution.
 When a conditional authorization depends on acceptance of residual risk above tolerance,
 the condition shall be supported by an approved Risk Acceptance Memo under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and the corresponding Risk Register entry before the authorization decision is rendered.
 Conditions shall be tracked through the Corrective Action Plan lifecycle under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 when they require milestone-based remediation.
 The IT Director may revoke a conditional authorization at any time if conditions are not met within the specified timeframe or if the risk posture deteriorates.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Denial of Authorization
\series default
:
 Issued when controls are inadequate and residual risk exceeds tolerance without acceptable compensating controls.
 The IT Director shall prohibit production operation of any system that receives a denial of authorization.
 The Assistant IT Director shall route the underlying deficiencies to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 for Corrective Action Plan development.
 A system that has been denied authorization may be resubmitted for review after remediation is verified through the assessment mechanisms defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Authorization Decision Record
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The Assistant IT Director shall document each authorization decision in the System of Engagement as an authorization decision record containing,
 at minimum:
 the system or control name and identifier;
 the security categorization and CJI indicator;
 the decision outcome and authorization effective date;
 the assessment results summary relied upon;
 the risk rationale supporting the decision;
 any conditions attached to a conditional authorization,
 with cross-references to the corresponding Corrective Action Plan tracked under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 and the corresponding Risk Register entry maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.09"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
;
 the IT Director's approval;
 and revocation status,
 where applicable.
 The Assistant IT Director shall retain authorization decision records in accordance with Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.4 Reauthorization and Revocation
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Authorization decisions remain valid until a subsequent event requires the IT Director to render a new decision.
 The following events shall trigger a reauthorization review:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The annual assessment cycle conducted under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 produces findings that change the risk posture of an authorized system.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A change to the system boundary,
 architecture,
 data classification,
 or control posture that alters the system's risk profile occurs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
The IT Director determines that a change in the threat environment,
 regulatory landscape,
 or operational context warrants reauthorization.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\lang english
A Corrective Action Plan associated with a conditional authorization fails to achieve closure within the approved timeframe.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Where the IT Director invokes the discretionary trigger described in the preceding list,
 the IT Director shall document the basis,
 source evidence,
 affected system,
 and required review deadline in the resulting authorization decision record.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall conduct an annual review of all active authorization decisions to confirm that no preceding trigger has been missed during the review period.
 Where the annual review identifies a missed trigger,
 the IT Director shall render a reauthorization decision following the process defined in Sections 6.1 and 6.2.
 Where no missed trigger is identified,
 the Assistant IT Director shall document the annual review outcome in the corresponding authorization decision records.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall render a new authorization decision following the same process defined in Sections 6.1 and 6.2.
 The Assistant IT Director shall mark the prior authorization decision record as superseded;
 retention of superseded records is governed by Section 6.6.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director may revoke an existing authorization at any time when the risk posture requires immediate action,
 without waiting for a reauthorization trigger.
 The Assistant IT Director shall document a revocation as a new authorization decision record with Denial of Authorization as the outcome,
 and the documentation shall include the risk rationale for immediate action.
\end_layout

