\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.6 Records Retention
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The authorization decision record is the authoritative record of each authorization decision rendered under this policy.
 The Assistant IT Director shall apply retention periods in accordance with NRS 239.125 and the Nevada Local Government Records Retention Schedule.
 The Assistant IT Director shall classify authorization decision records in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.11"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Authorization Decision Records
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall retain authorization decision records,
 including conditions attached to conditional authorizations,
 supporting risk rationale,
 and superseded prior records,
 for a minimum of three (3) calendar years from the end of the calendar year in which the decision was rendered,
 in accordance with LRDA 20071256 (Quality Assurance Review Audits and Reports).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Destruction Standards
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall ensure destruction of confidential authorization decision records complies with NAC 239.165.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Legal Holds
\series default
:
 The Assistant IT Director shall suspend retention and disposition actions for authorization decision records during litigation holds,
 public records preservation requirements,
 ongoing audits,
 external investigations,
 or other legal hold events,
 in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
